, read first time and referred to Committee on
2026 RR 3513/DI JR

Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION recognizing the partnership
2 between Ontario, Canada, and the State of Indiana.
3 Whereas, The State of Indiana and the Province of Ontario
4 have long enjoyed friendly relations, our economies mutually
5 benefitting from each other;
6 Whereas, Canadians have played a large role in Indiana's
7 economy, with goods traded between Ontario and Indiana
8 being worth more than $26.2 billion in 2022;
9 Whereas, In 2023, Ontario was Indiana's largest export
10 destination, supporting over 1.5 million jobs in Ontario;
11 Whereas, In 2024, Ontario and Indiana entered into a
12 memorandum of understanding to highlight cooperation in
13 economic development, workforce development, and regulatory
14 coordination;
15 Whereas, Recently, Canadian Solar announced plans to
16 locate its second U.S. solar module production facility in
17 Jeffersonville, Indiana, an investment projected at $800 million
18 and creating up to 1,200 new jobs;
2026 RR 3513/DI JR

2
1 Whereas, Recently, Nova Chemicals Corporation also
2 announced plans to establish a mechanical recycling facility in
3 Connersville, creating up to 125 new jobs; and
4 Whereas, Indiana and Ontario have a history of being
5 strong partners through bilateral trade and a shared vision of
6 the future: Therefore,
7 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
8 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
9 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate recognizes the
10 partnership between Ontario and Indiana.
11 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
12 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the Ontario Trade and
13 Investment Office co-located in the Consulate General of
14 Canada in Chicago.
2026 RR 3513/DI JR

